Rating: 3
I like this for apple crisp lovers - to surprise them a bit and for a bit more crunch in the topping, which never hurts!

Rating: 3
I have made this a few times.I don't use granny smiths, I find they shrink too much. I use a medly of apples, whatever looks good at the grocery store. I don't cut them thin, I cut them thick so I don't end up with apple mush. I replace some of the white flour in the topping with oatmeal that I grind in the blender. And I sub 1 & 1/2 TB of cornstarch for the flour that is mixed with the apples. Sometimes I tossed in a bit of grated fresh ginger. YUMMM

Rating: 4
I love this recipe! I substituted oats for the almonds, increased sugar to 1 cup, omitted the lemon peel, decreased nutmeg to 1/4 tsp and used Cortland apples. Delicious!!!

Rating: 4
My husband and I both thought this was delicious. I left out the almond extract and added a little more vanilla instead. I'll definitely make this again!

Rating: 3
I made this for my brother and me while my parents were away in Mexico! I forgot to peel the apples but it still was really good, i think it may have added a little touch! He didn't want any almonds (picky) so I used regular old oats and it turned out just delicious! It took a little longer than 1 hour, about 15-20 minutes more. We topped it with praline ice cream, It was awesome!!! I'll make it (for him) again for sure :)

